{"000-section": {"000-title": "Kerala Sama Education Plan for Kudumbashree Members \u2013 State Literacy Mission Authority"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Kerala State Literacy Mission to start Sama Education Plan for Kudumbashree workers, 1 lakh members to make registration to apply online for edu programme, classes for 10th & 12th equivalency course to start in January 2020"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Kerala Sama Education Plan for Kudumbashree Workers", "001-normal": "Out of 48 lakh Kudumbashree workers in Kerala, around 1 lakh members will be enrolled in class 10 & class 12 equivalency courses in Sama Edu Plan. Literacy Mission has introduced Sama Education Plan as a part of its women empowerment project in association with Kudumbasree. All the interested persons can apply online for enrollment in Sama education programme b/w 17 Dec to 31 December 2019 to attend classes in January next year.", "002-normal": "Sama Education programme aims to provide min. 10th class qualification to members of Kudumbashree mission. Literacy Mission will arrange classes in 1,000 local bodies across the state. There would be 2 batches of 50 members each attending the classes. There will be 2,000 central coordinators for Kerala Sama Education Scheme 2019-2020, one for each equivalency course at each centre.", "003-normal": "The course fee and examination fees for the candidates would be paid by the respective self governing bodies. Kudumbashree members who were qualified to teach will be given preference in order to conduct the classes efficiently. Kerala State Literacy Mission is already collecting the details of candidates from Kudumbashree. These includes workers who could not complete their education due to various reasons and are willing to make registration for Sama Education Plan.", "004-normal": "Equivalency programmes are organised in view of providing an alternative education that is equivalent to the existing formal system of education, be it related to formal or vocational education. This programme is targeted towards those neo-literates who aspires to continue their education and acquire certificate that would place them equal standing with others who have successfully completed their studies from the formal system of education.", "005-normal": "Source / Reference Link: https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/thiruvananthapuram/cm-to-launch-sama-edu-plan-tomorrow-to-benefit-1l-workers/articleshow/72702273.cms"}}